reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 9, 2023
reviews.reviewText: Exactly as advertised - I love when that happens! Super cushy, non-skid bottom and an absolute must-have if you have a job that requires you to sit for long periods of time. Actually, I'd recommend this to anyone that just wants a more comfortable chair.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 13, 2021
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great for with short drivers! I’m only 5’0” and this is amazing.
reviews.reviewText: I’m 5’0” and have short legs. I bought this to use in my SUV (see photo) and it definitely does the trick. I wanted something soft and comfortable but not too soft that it would squish down and not give me the boost I needed. This cushion does the trick. It’s wide enough and very soft but lifts me just over 2 inches so I can see over the steering wheel more easily. I’m sure after lots of use it’ll squish down but this definitely helps right now. I also tried a more standard wedge type cushion which made it a bit easier to reach the foot pedals but didn’t raise me up enough. With this cushion I can adjust the seat forward and still reach the pedals easily. This one also doesn’t slide and I do have to do some wiggling to get seated right when I get in but that’s to be expected with a giant cushion on top the seat.Bottom line, this is a giant squishy seat that’s great for us shorty drivers.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on June 10, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Very Soft and Squishy
reviews.reviewText: This is an extremely soft and cushy cushion. It looks high, but for a 200 pound person, it will compress down to just about 1" high. The design also has grooves that would suggest that it supports you in a stable position like a car seat. It's so squishy that this is not the case. I actually feel somewhat unstable sitting on it. If you're looking for softness, this may be a good choice. However, if you need more additional height and stable support, this may not be the perfect choice.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 24, 2023
reviews.reviewText: I needed a booster seat to see over the hood due to the seats of the newer vehicles being tilted towards the back. This is the highest one I could find, it’s comfortable and adds enough height for me.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 8, 2023
reviews.reviewText: Value and shape is average. Stability is below average, and quality is good. Only big negative is it flattens out easily. Might be ok if your weight is around 175 and below. It does return to its original shape quickly after using it.

reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars A GREAT Cushie for my Tushie
reviews.reviewText: This cushion is BETTER than what the description says. I have stage 4 arthritis in my entire back, (from C1 to AS). With Stenosis, Spondylitis, Sciatica and S shape Scoliosis. reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 15, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars PASS! Worst seat cushion, ever. If your rear end is large, don't bother!
reviews.reviewText: This cushion is so ridiculously bad, it's hard to know where to begin! It arrived promptly but that's where the good stuff ended. When I took it out of the box, it was awkwardly folded in half like the thickest taco you've ever seen. A day later it was still curled up that direction and we had to force it flat on a chair in order to even test it. And it was SO UNCOMFORTABLE AND TINY!From the description it seemed to me that this was a cushion specifically designed for larger individuals of higher-than-normal weight, with latex instead of memory foam, more dense and extra tall so it wouldn't flatten out when sat upon by larger folks. I have a latex mattress topper that I adore, so I thought maybe this was the answer to my hopes: a squishy but firm chair cushion that wouldn't just bottom out as soon as I sat down like memory foam ones always do. Here's the rub: they got the dense and tall part right.... just not the other two dimensions!Unlike their photos, and unlike the other user photos, the cover felt loose, like it was designed for something larger and now this latex piece was slipping around in there. So it feels unstable as soon as you sit down because it all might slip out of place within its own cover. Additionally, it's incredibly small in both width and depth. So as I sat down, not only did I feel like I'd slip, but also I felt like I would literally TIP OVER SIDEWAYS IN MY CHAIR! What the heck? So there was really no way for me to get comfortable at all in the dang thing. NO THANKS!I'd say the only thing it's good for is as a booster seat for a short, small person trying to drive a giant car.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United Kingdom on September 16, 2020
reviews.reviewText: I work behind an office desk for over 10 hours a day which has really affected my lower back and tailbone. I am always in discomfort when I am working - making it hard to concentrate even. A new expensive office chair did not help me either. The moment I sat on this seat cushion though I felt a wave of relief. It is large and firm enough to give me support, while soft enough that I can sink into and not feel pain in my tailbone any more. I have tried other cushions prior to this but nothing compares to this seat cushion. Its a godsend - so comfy!
